ZH: 不要逼我做我不想做的事情。
EN: Don't force me to do something I don't want to do.

ZH: 他逼着他妹妹练习钢琴。
EN: He pressures his younger sister to practice the piano.

ZH: 老板逼员工加班。
EN: The boss pushes the employees to work overtime.

ZH: 我们不应该逼孩子学习他们不感兴趣的东西。
EN: We shouldn't force kids to learn things they're not interested in.

ZH: 这个任务逼迫他们团结合作。
EN: This task forces them to work together.

ZH: 情况逼迫我们做出艰难的决定。
EN: The situation compels us to make tough decisions.

ZH: 公司的竞争逼得我们不得不升级技术。
EN: The competition from other companies forces us to upgrade our technology.

ZH: 警察逼问嫌疑人。
EN: The police interrogate the suspect.

ZH: 这个难题逼得他们想尽办法。
EN: This difficult problem pushes them to come up with solutions.

ZH: 她的父母逼她嫁给一个她不爱的人。
EN: Her parents pressure her to marry someone she doesn't love.

ZH: 老板逼他赶快完成项目。
EN: The boss urges him to finish the project quickly.

ZH: 学校要求逼学生参加校运动会。
EN: The school requires students to participate in the school sports day.

ZH: 这个小组内部逼力强大。
EN: There is strong internal pressure within this group.

ZH: 她的表现逼得她成为最佳选手。
EN: Her performance pushed her to become the top player.

ZH: 我们不能逼任何人接受我们的观点。
EN: We shouldn't force anyone to accept our views.

ZH: 这场比赛逼得球员们拼尽全力。
EN: This game pushes the players to give it their all.

ZH: 广告逼着人们购买他们不需要的东西。
EN: Advertisements pressure people to buy things they don't need.

ZH: 他们的关系逼着他们分开。
EN: Their relationship forces them apart.

ZH: 这个决定逼迫我们认真考虑后果。
EN: This decision compels us to consider the consequences carefully.

ZH: 妈妈逼他去睡觉。
EN: Mom is urging him to go to bed.
